[SN]TITLE[SN]
Runner dies after being hit by car in Tamworth

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man out running has died after being hit by a car.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The jogger was struck as he ran along the A51 Tamedrive, in Tamworth, Staffordshire, on Friday morning. He was pronounced dead at the scene.
The driver of the car involved, a grey Audi, was uninjured. The road was closed, between the Bolebridge Island to Lichfield Street, during the morning for investigation work.
Police would like any witnesses to contact them.
